  = section "People from Adjectives" do
    %p For the most part any adjective used to describe people can also be used to refer to people with zero derivation, simply treating the adjectival form as a noun to mean “person who is X” or ”people who are X”.

  = section "Nouns from Adjectives" do
    %p For forming abstract nouns from adjectives, the most common suffix used in Tunisian is <i>-(i)tâ</i>. The form <i>-tâ</i> is the default, with <i>-itâ</i> generally being used when the stem ends in a consonant cluster. It is common for stems ending in -iC- to undergo metathesis to -Ci- before this suffix.
